        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:11PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cross, or 10 miles north of Tilden, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tilden, Calliham, Crowther, and Cross.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
